@baden_coalition_menu

- @spd_majority_baden
- @weimar_coalition_baden
- @grand_coalition_baden
- @bourgeois_coalition_baden
- @left_coalition_baden
- @social_catholic_coalition_baden
- @no_coalition_baden
- @baden_coalition_creator

@spd_majority_baden
title: SPD majority
subtitle: We can govern alone
view-if: spd_r_baden >= 50
on-arrival: baden_election_2_trigger_time = time + 48; catholic_spd += 1; catholic_z -= 2; rural_spd += 1; rural_others -= 2; baden_gov = "SPD"

@weimar_coalition_baden
title: A Weimar Coalition will be formed
choose-if: weimar_coalition_baden >= 50 and z_relation >= 30
on-arrival: baden_election_2_trigger_time = time + 48; z_relation += 1; ddp_relation += 1; baden_gov = "Weimar"

@grand_coalition_baden
title: A Grand Coalition will be formed
choose-if: grand_coalition_baden >= 50 and z_relation >= 25 and dvp_relation >= 40
on-arrival: baden_election_2_trigger_time = time + 48; z_relation += 2; dvp_relation += 3; baden_gov = "Grand"

@bourgeois_coalition_baden
title: A bourgeois coalition must be formed
choose-if: true_bourgeois_coalition_baden > 50
view-if: (weimar_coalition_baden < 50 and z_relation <= 30 and right_coalition_baden < 50) or kpd_relation >= 60
on-arrival: baden_election_2_trigger_time = time + 48; baden_gov = "Bourgeois"

@left_coalition_baden
title: A Coalition of the Left will be formed
subtitle: We will work alongside the KPD
choose-if: left_coalition_badenn >= 50 and kpd_relation >= 65
on-arrival: baden_election_2_trigger_time = time + 48; ruarl_kpd += 3; rural_others -= 2; catholic_dvp -= 1; catholic_spd += 1; baden_gov = "Left"

@right_wing_coalition_baden
title: The right forms a government...
subtitle: This doesn't make sense.
choose-if: right_coalition_baden >= 50
view-if: right_coalition_baden >= 50
on-arrival: baden_election_2_trigger_time = time + 48; rural_nsdap += 2; dvp_relation -= 5; baden_gov = "Right"

This can't end well...

@social_catholic_coalition_baden
title: Why not form a <span style="color: [+ spd_colour +];">**Social**</span>-<span style="color: [+ z_colour +];">**Catholic**</span> Coalition?
choose-if: (z_r_baden + spd_r_baden) >= 50 and z_relation >= 40 and ddp_r_baden <= 5.5
on-arrival: baden_election_2_trigger_time = time + 48; z_relation += 2; ddp_relation -= 2; baden_gov = "Social-Catholic"

The poor performance of the <span style="color: [+ ddp_colour +];">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> has allowed us to try a <span style="color: [+ spd_colour +];">**Social**</span>-<span style="color: [+ z_colour +];">**Catholic**</span> Coalition.
  
@no_coalition_baden
title: There is no possible government arrangement
subtitle: New elections will be called...
on-arrival: baden_election_2_trigger_time = time + 3; rural_dnvp += 2
view-if: (grand_coalition_baden < 50 or z_relation < 30) and right_coalition_baden < 50
  
  

@baden_coalition_creator
title: Custom Coalition Creator (Test)
subtitle: It seems to work in GTS, doesn't it?
on-arrival: baden_coalition_r = spr_r_baden

Current support: [+ baden_coalition_r +]%

